---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SnailGlyph from '@/components/SnailGlyph.astro';
import Asterism from '@/components/Asterism.astro';
import SectionMark from '@/components/SectionMark.astro';

const title = 'About — HiQ Cortex';
const description =
  'HiQ Cortex is a thin intelligence layer above every LCA database, built by HiQ-AI. This is why we made it, and why the mascot is a snail.';
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative">
    <div class="container-page pt-14 md:pt-20 pb-14">
      <div class="mb-10 flex items-baseline justify-between border-b border-rule pb-4">
        <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
        <p class="running-footer">{new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10)}</p>
      </div>
      <h1 class="font-display" style="font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 5rem); line-height: 1.02; letter-spacing: -0.025em; font-variation-settings: 'SOFT' 40, 'opsz' 144; font-weight: 400; max-width: 18ch;">
        Slow, on purpose.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-10 max-w-2xl font-serif italic" style="font-size: 1.22rem; line-height: 1.55; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 20; color: var(--ink-mute);">
        HiQ Cortex is a thin layer of intelligence sitting above every LCA database,
        methodology, and calculation tool. This is what we're trying to do, and why the
        mascot is a snail.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- In one paragraph -->
  <section class="border-t border-rule">
    <div class="container-page py-16 md:py-20">
      <div class="grid gap-12 md:grid-cols-[1fr_1.2fr] md:gap-16 items-start">
        <div class="text-ink-500" style="color: var(--ink);">
          <SnailGlyph class="w-full max-w-sm" />
          <p class="margin-note mt-6">
            <em>Cornu aspersum</em>, rendered with its house on its back and its trail behind it.
            The animal is the argument: slow, self-documenting, legible in the evidence it leaves.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="max-w-2xl">
          <SectionMark kicker="The company" numeral="I" title="HiQ-AI, in one paragraph." />
          <p class="font-serif" style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 20; color: var(--ink);">
            We build carbon accounting infrastructure for LCA practitioners, corporate sustainability
            teams, and the auditors who review their work. Our product, <strong>HiQ Cortex</strong>,
            is a reasoning layer above every major LCA database — HiQLCD, Ecoinvent, EF, CarbonMinds,
            and more — that turns natural-language questions into cited, DQI-scored, audit-grade
            answers. Two surfaces: <a href="/product/chat">Cortex Chat</a> in the browser and
            <a href="/product/cowork">Cortex Cowork</a> on your desktop.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why we built this -->
  <section class="border-t border-rule" style="background: var(--paper-rim);">
    <div class="container-page py-20 md:py-24">
      <SectionMark kicker="Why we built it" numeral="II" title="LCA's bottleneck is not data volume." />

      <div class="max-w-3xl space-y-6 font-serif" style="font-size: 1.08rem; line-height: 1.7; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 20; color: var(--ink);">
        <p>
          The global supply of life cycle inventory data now runs into the millions of records.
          The problem has never been whether the number exists somewhere. The problem is this:
          who reads the question right. Who translates a real production process into the right
          retrieval language. Who navigates a dozen database vocabularies to judge whether a
          given emission factor can defensibly be used for a given commission.
        </p>
        <p>
          Traditionally, that work belongs to experienced practitioners — expensive, scarce,
          hard to replicate. <strong>Cortex is our answer.</strong> A thin layer of intelligence
          sitting above all the databases and methodologies, compressing
          <em>understand → search → cross-check → auditable answer</em> into a single conversation.
        </p>
        <p>
          It does not replace experts. It scales their judgment.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The snail -->
  <section class="border-t border-rule">
    <div class="container-page py-20 md:py-24">
      <SectionMark kicker="The mascot" numeral="III" title="Why a snail, when every AI company picks a rocket." />

      <div class="max-w-3xl space-y-6 font-serif" style="font-size: 1.08rem; line-height: 1.7; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 20; color: var(--ink);">
        <p>
          We chose the opposite of the industry default on purpose.
        </p>
        <p>
          The AI image today is a lightning bolt, a rocket, a neuron — fast, strong, all-knowing.
          LCA has never been that kind of industry. A single CBAM filing is built out of weeks
          of boundary debates, BOM decomposition, and trade-offs among a dozen databases. Every
          step must be auditable, challenged, and traced. What a client actually needs is not
          "answered quickly," but "answered correctly — and able to explain why."
        </p>
        <p>
          The snail is the shape of that work.
        </p>
      </div>

      <Asterism />

      <div class="grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-3 mt-6">
        <article class="font-serif" style="line-height: 1.65; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 18; color: var(--ink);">
          <div class="eyebrow mb-3" style="color: var(--shell);">Slow</div>
          <p>
            It won't skip the boundary discussion to hand you a number. Every answer waits until
            the right questions have been asked: system boundary, allocation rule, geographic fit.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="font-serif" style="line-height: 1.65; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 18; color: var(--ink);">
          <div class="eyebrow mb-3" style="color: var(--shell);">Shell</div>
          <p>
            It carries its home wherever it goes. Every cited dataset, every proxy assumption,
            every version switch stays attached to the answer. Reviewers see what Cortex saw.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="font-serif" style="line-height: 1.65; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 18; color: var(--ink);">
          <div class="eyebrow mb-3" style="color: var(--shell);">Trail</div>
          <p>
            It leaves marks behind it. Regulators, auditors, and legal teams can follow the trail
            back to the origin. The line between a conversation and an audit-grade report is the product.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>

      <blockquote class="mx-auto mt-20 max-w-3xl text-center">
        <p class="pullquote">
          Cortex does the fastest things on the backend. What it delivers is always the slowest thing:
          <em style="color: var(--shell); font-style: italic;">a chain of reasoning you can audit, line by line.</em>
        </p>
        <footer class="eyebrow mt-6">Slow is the most important promise we can make.</footer>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Open interfaces -->
  <section class="border-t border-rule" style="background: var(--paper-rim);">
    <div class="container-page py-20 md:py-24">
      <SectionMark kicker="Open interfaces" numeral="IV" title="REST, MCP, AG-UI, A2A." />
      <p class="max-w-3xl font-serif" style="font-size: 1.08rem; line-height: 1.65; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 20; color: var(--ink);">
        Cortex is built on open protocols. If you'd rather call it from your own tool than
        through our chat, the integration surface is already there. See the
        <a href="/docs">docs</a> or email us.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Contact -->
  <section class="border-t border-rule">
    <div class="container-prose py-24 text-center">
      <h2 class="font-display" style="font-variation-settings: 'SOFT' 40, 'opsz' 96; font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem); line-height: 1.02; letter-spacing: -0.02em;">
        Come work on the slow answer.
      </h2>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-8 max-w-xl font-serif italic" style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.55; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 20; color: var(--ink-mute);">
        Questions, partnerships, or a bug report — email us.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="mailto:contact@hiq.earth" class="ticket">contact@hiq.earth</a>
        <a href="/product/chat" class="ticket-ghost">See what Cortex does</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
